      <body>A very basic initial implementation can be found at &lt;git://github.com/dasch/rails.git&gt;.

Currently, you have to do
&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;bzr init myproject
cd myproject
rails . --bzr&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

I need to hook into the application generator, doing a &lt;code&gt;bzr init&lt;/code&gt; before anything is added. Furthermore, in the &quot;add file&quot; generator, I need to know the name of the project's root directory, i.e. &lt;code&gt;/path/to/myproject&lt;/code&gt;, so I can do &lt;code&gt;bzr add &lt;em&gt;filename&lt;/em&gt; &lt;em&gt;/path/to/myproject&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/code&gt;, because otherwise the user has to be in the project root directory.</body>
